# How do you prioritize your tasks when you have multiple deadlines?

When managing multiple deadlines, I prioritize tasks based on both urgency and business impact. I typically evaluate which tasks directly affect users, system stability, or project delivery timelines, and then organize my work accordingly using task management tools.

For example, during my time as a FullStack Engineer at MimosaTEK, I was responsible for both developing new features for user-facing applications and maintaining internal systems. I prioritized tasks that had the highest impact on user experience and business value, such as delivering new features that improved engagement and supported company growth. At the same time, I ensured critical maintainance issues were addressed promptly to maintain system reliability.

After defining priorities, I broke down larger tasks into smaller actionable steps and used Larksuite to track deadlines, and progress. I also allocated dedicated time blocks for feature development while reserving time for maintainace and unexpected issues. This structured approach helped me stay organized, avoid burnout, and consistently meet deadlines without compromising quality.

Overall, my strategy is to combine clear prioritization based on urgency and impact with structured planning and continuous reassessment as priorities evolve.
